  <div class="card">
    <div class="ct">What the model has learned</div>
    <div class="ins" style="border-color:#0F6E56"><span class="ins-lbl" style="color:#0F6E56">Skating: most reliably transferable skill</span>Acceleration + edgework convert at 2.4× the rate of static skills. Every franchise-tier player in the database has skating averaging 8.5+.</div>
    <div class="ins" style="border-color:#185FA5"><span class="ins-lbl" style="color:#185FA5">Playmaking vision: best predictor of stardom</span>Crosby (10), Hughes (10), Makar (10), MacKinnon (9) — not one franchise player has vision below 9.</div>
    <div class="ins" style="border-color:#BA7517"><span class="ins-lbl" style="color:#BA7517">Compete/motor: rescues undersized players</span>Konecny (5-10/175), Jarvis (5-10/179), Stankoven (5-8/168) all overcame size with elite compete + skating.</div>
    <div class="ins" style="border-color:#D85A30"><span class="ins-lbl" style="color:#D85A30">Size without skating = strongest bust predictor</span>Big players with skating below 6.0 fail at 70%+ rate in the database.</div>
    <div class="ins" style="border-color:#A32D2D"><span class="ins-lbl" style="color:#A32D2D">Decision speed: the AHL trap</span>Most common reason prospects stall. Hard to develop post-draft. Low marks here are a ceiling, not a development area.</div>
